
Rootin Tootin is a fast RESTful MVC web framework that is written in D. It is 
designed to scale well by default, while still providing a developer experience 
similar to Ruby on Rails.

Documentation is generated with RoboDoc:
robodoc --src src/ --doc html/ --multidoc --index --html --tabsize 4 --documenttitle "Rootin Tootin 0.7 API"

See http://rootin.toot.in for details.


1. Install the dependencies for your distro:
# ubuntu
sudo apt-get install python-mysqldb python-pexpect \
python-mako mysql-client mysql-server libmysqlclient16-dev build-essential \
ldc libtango-ldc-dev libpcre3-dev libfcgi-dev inotify-tools
sudo service mysql start

# fedora
# Install ldc and tango from here:
# http://www.dsource.org/projects/ldc/
sudo yum groupinstall "Development Tools"
sudo yum install redhat-lsb MySQL-python pexpect \
python-mako mysql mysql-devel mysql-server ldc pcre-devel fcgi-devel \
tango-devel inotify-tools redhat-lsb
sudo service mysqld start


2. Install Rootin Tootin from source
cd ~
wget http://launchpad.net/rester/trunk/0.7.0/+download/rootintootin-0.7.0.tar.gz
tar -zxvf rootintootin-0.7.0.tar.gz
cd rootintootin-0.7.0
sudo make install


3. Copy the examples to your desktop, to play with:
cp -r examples/ ~/Desktop/examples/
cd ~/Desktop/examples/users


4. Configure and run the user example:
./gen configure development database user:root password:letmein
./gen configure development server port:3000
./gen recreate development database
./gen migrate development
./run


6. Navigate your web browser to http://localhost:3000/users and you should 
see a basic CRUD example.



